
@RestController - contains / wrapps @Controller @ResponseBody


Returning ResponseEntity<T> vs PlainDto
- we can send PlainDto in the get mapping. Since we have @RestController annotated, SpringMVC will serialize
the dto object to JSON.
- Returning ResponseEntity<T> allows us more control of what we are sending with the dto, such as statuscode or messages
    ex. new ResponseEntity<>(PlanDto, HttpStatus.OK);

@PathVariable is optional if the {vairableName} matches the method argument names
@GetMapping("/{beerId}")
public ResponseEntity<BeerDto> getBeer(@PathVariable UUID beerId)




